## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## board_smoke.bot
##
## End-to-end smoke for the bot capabilities -> __mcp-board stdio
## MCP server (Task A in .plans/board-capabilities-next-steps.md).
##
## A single claude_code agent is granted board.{read,create,move}.
## At run time, the runtime registers the internal __mcp-board MCP
## server and extends AllowedTools with mcp__iterion_board__*. The
## agent then performs three deterministic tool calls:
##
##   1. mcp__iterion_board__create_issue (title: "Smoke A …")
##   2. mcp__iterion_board__create_issue (title: "Smoke B …")
##   3. mcp__iterion_board__transition_issue (id: A, to: "ready")
##
## Run:
##   ./iterion run bots/smoke/board_smoke.bot \
##       --store-dir /tmp/iterion-board-smoke
##
## Verify:
##   ./iterion issue list  --store-dir /tmp/iterion-board-smoke
##   ./iterion issue board --store-dir /tmp/iterion-board-smoke
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

schema smoke_output:
  first_id:   string
  second_id:  string
  summary:    string

prompt smoke_system:
  You are exercising the iterion native kanban board through its MCP
  server. You MUST perform EXACTLY these three tool calls, in order,
  and NOTHING else (no Read, no Bash, no Glob, no Grep):

    1. mcp__iterion_board__create_issue
         title: "Smoke A - board capabilities create"
         body:  "First issue created by board_smoke.bot."
         state: "backlog"

    2. mcp__iterion_board__create_issue
         title: "Smoke B - board capabilities create"
         body:  "Second issue created by board_smoke.bot."
         state: "backlog"

    3. mcp__iterion_board__transition_issue
         id:    <identifier returned by step 1>
         to:    "ready"

  After step 3, return the structured smoke_output with first_id and
  second_id set to the identifiers you received from create_issue,
  and a one-sentence summary describing what you did.

prompt smoke_user:
  Run the three-step board smoke test now. Do not ask questions.

agent smoke:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model:   "claude-opus-4-8"
  output:  smoke_output
  system:  smoke_system
  user:    smoke_user
  capabilities: [board.read, board.create, board.move]
  tool_max_steps: 12

workflow board_smoke:
  entry: smoke
  smoke -> done
